title: New York Times Best Sellers Fiction November 30, 2014
description:
1. Revival, by Stephen King. (Scribner.)
2. Flesh and Blood, by Patricia Cornwell. (Morrow/HarperCollins.)
3. Gray Mountain, by John Grisham. (Doubleday.)
4. The Burning Room, by Michael Connelly. (Little, Brown.)
5. Gone Girl, by Gillian Flynn. (Crown.)
6. Blue Labyrinth, by Douglas Preston and Lincoln Child. (Grand Central.)
7. A Will and A Way, by Nora Roberts. (Silhouette.)
8. All The Light We Cannot See, by Anthony Doerr. (Scribner.)
9. Blood Magick, by Nora Roberts. (Berkley.)
10. Leaving Time, by Jodi Picoult. (Ballantine.)
11. Ice Cold, by Tess Gerritsen. (Ballantine.)
12. Kiss Of Christmas Magic, by Eve Langlais, Aubrey Rose, Molly Prince and others. (Swift River Media.)
13. Prince Lestat, by Anne Rice. (Knopf.)
14. His Secretary, by Melanie Marchande. (Melanie Marchande.)
15. Private India, by James Patterson and Ashwin Sanghi. (Grand Central.)
16. One Night Denied, by Jodi Ellen Malpas (Grand Central)
17. Orphan Train, by Christina Baker Kline (Morrow/HarperCollins)
18. Havana Storm, by Clive Cussler and Dirk Cussler. (Putnam.)
19. Fifty Shades of Grey, by E. L. James (Vintage)
20. Dark Places, by Gillian Flynn. (Broadway.)
